	Walgreen's has a beta of $1.0733$ and an alpha of $-.3471\%$.
	\begin{center}
		\begin{tabular}{ll}
			\multicolumn{2}{l}{Date $t=0$} \\ \hline
			1. & Short 1 USD worth of Walgreen's. \\
			2. & Borrow .0733 USD. \\
			3. & Use your 1.0733 USD to buy 1.0733 USD worth of market. \\ \hline
			\multicolumn{2}{l}{Date $t=1$} \\ \hline
			1. & Sell the market \\
			2. & Repay the loan \\
			3. & Cover your short \\ \hline
			\multicolumn{2}{l}{You should earn .3471 USD on average.}
		\end{tabular}
	\end{center}
\end{frame}

